14 SECTION 5.1.(d) Article 6B of Chapter 77 of the General Statutes, as enacted by
15 subsection (a) of this section and amended by subsections (b) and (c) of this section, is amended
16 by adding a new section to read:
17 "§ 77-89.9. Fees.
18 (a) Except as limited by any other provisions of State or federal law, the Commission
19 may assess fees related only to the following:
20 (1) Participation in education, training, or certification services provided by the
21 Commission.
22 (2) Use of facilities owned or operated by the Commission.
23 (3) Application for a permit administered by the Commission to regulate
24 privileged or special uses of Lake Norman and its shoreline area.
25 (b) In setting fee amounts to be charged for activities provided in subsection (a) of this
26 section, the Commission shall not do any of the following:
27 (1) Set a fee in an excessive amount that is neither reasonable nor customary for
28 the services and privileges provided by the Commission.
29 (2) Set a fee in an amount that exceeds the Commission's actual costs for the
30 service provided.
31 (3) Charge fees for general access to or use of Lake Norman or its shoreline area.
32 (4) Discriminate on the basis of race, color, sex, religious creed, or national origin.
33 (c) Each year by January 31, the Commission shall produce a publicly available and
34 auditable report that includes an accounting of all of its fee collections and funding from other
35 sources compared to its program-specific expenses during the prior calendar year. This annual
36 financial report shall include adequate detail to determine that the Commission has met each of
37 the requirements of this section, accompanied by a formal written certification of the same by
38 the chair of the Commission. If there is a surplus of fee collections or funding in a given calendar
39 year, it shall be applied to program-specific expenses for the next calendar year."
